Signal weighted:

$$y_{ijt} \sim N(\alpha_i\theta_j, \frac{1}{a_i})$$
Where:

$\alpha_i$ : Student Reliability
$\theta_j$ : Teacher Effect
$a_i$ : Student Sensitivity (how responsive they are to the teacher)



```{r}
library(rstan)

# Create integer IDs for Stan
edu_subset$student_idx <- as.integer(as.factor(edu_subset$CHILDID))
edu_subset$teacher_idx <- as.integer(as.factor(edu_subset$T4_ID))

stan_data <- list(
  N = nrow(edu_subset),
  S = length(unique(edu_subset$CHILDID)),
  T = length(unique(edu_subset$T4_ID)),
  student_id = edu_subset$student_idx,
  teacher_id = edu_subset$teacher_idx,
  y = edu_subset$post_test,
  # Add other covariates (pre-test, SES, etc.) as a matrix if needed
  x = as.matrix(edu_subset[, c("pre_test", "ses")]) 
)
```



```{r}
fit <- stan(file = "sw_stan.stan", data = stan_data, iter = 100, chains = 4)
# Extract Teacher Effects
teacher_results <- summary(fit, pars = "theta")$summary
```
